During the time-lapsed image acquisition, samples were kept in focus by means of implementation into the acquisition software of one of the general auto-focus algorithms. Image contrast is optimal when a histogram of intensity values shows a broad distribution over all bins. This characteristic feature can be approximated by the standard deviation of pixel intensity values. For each image, contrast was enhanced by histogram equalization, and standard deviation was calculated. A normalized focus index (FI) was defined by dividing the standard deviation of the original image (SDoriginal) by the standard deviation of the contrast enhanced image (SDenhanced): \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
