$$ {\text{FI}} = \frac{{{\text{SD}}_{{{\text{original}}}} }} {{{\text{SD}}_{{{\text{enhanced}}}} }} $$\end{document}For each cell, a series of images was captured at five different heights. The image was then defined to be in focus at the vertical level of maximal normalized focus. This height (z) was used as the central level when capturing the z-series in the next time step, thus allowing gradual vertical shift during the time-lapsed image acquisition. Finally, a stack of time-lapsed images was constructed for each x, y-position and analyzed off-line.
